column5: The index number is unique for each of 35245 VDT records received from DxD inc.
This random ID was produced in the de-identification process. A "Customer" is a unique individual within Ohio's Bureau of Motor Vehicles Licensing System.
column7: A uuid operator was acted upon the distinct Customer ID set and a random alpha-numeric string was produced for each Customer ID.

column5: Age of customer at time of virtual driving test.
column7: A date difference function was used to calculate age in days. This utilizes the follow fields: DOB and DateStart . TestDate - DateStart = AgeAtExam. DateStart indicates the day the virtual driving test was administered.

column5: Indicate in which year the VDT test was performed.
Gender originates from the Ohio Driver's License System. As there are multiple entries per customer,the latest gender was taken as the correct gender.
Score is the scored result of a maneuverability or driving test. This is an numeric score stored in the Ohio licensing system.
A binary 1 or 0 field. 1 indicates Ohio deemed this test a passing exam. 0 indicates Ohio deemed this test a failure. This variables is stored in the Ohio licensing system.
The order of Maneuver tests completed for the same customer, derived from date/time.
The number of Maneuver tests a customer had taken in history up to the data pull date.
This is an honest brokered ID for the BMV examiner who conducted the maneuver test.
Score is the scored result of a maneuverability or driving test. This is an numeric score stored in the Ohio licensing system.
A binary 1 or 0 field. 1 indicates Ohio deemed this test a passing exam. 0 indicates Ohio deemed this test a failure. This variable is stored in the Ohio licensing system.
The order of Driving tests completed for the same customer, derived from date/time.
The number of driving tests a customer has taken in history up to the data pull date.
This is an honest brokered ID for the BMV examiner who conducted the driving test.
The order of VDT tests completed for the same customer, derived from date/time.
Ohio driver license class indicates if it?s a non-commercial or commercial license.
License type indicates if it?s a temporary permit (learner permit) or full license.
This is the date the OBMV issued a customer a full driver license (not a temporary permit license)
Indicates how many days a customer spent in the related learner?s permit as of the date they attempted an on road test.
Customer?s age at the beginning of their first learner?s permit.
Customer?s age at the issuance of their current learner?s permit as of the VDT date;
Customer?s age at their first attempted on road exam in their current learner?s permit period as of the VDT date
Customer?s age at their last attempted on road exam in their current learner?s permit period as of the VDT date.
The sequence order of current learner?s permit associated with VDT for each customer
The number of temporary permits (learner permits: license type=G) the customer has been issued in the entire history of the Ohio licensing database up to the data pull date.
Customer?s age at their first on road exam among any of their learner?s permit periods.
Customer?s age at their last on road exam among any of their learner?s permit period.
This flag indicates if a customer had a full license (license type O) before they took the VDT.
A flag indicating if this person has information on driving school name in the dataset.
The date a customer completed driving school education.
This is a VDT summary score, derived using time series channel data as described in the JMIR paper by Grethlein et al (2020).
This is a VDT summary score, derived using variable data as described in the JMIR paper by Grethlein et al (2020).
This is ranged length from diver license issue date to end of crash data cut off date.
This is the lower range of RangeOfLicensure in days.
This is the higher range of RangeOfLicensure in days.
Age of customer at time of vehicle crash.
This is the severity of the crash based on the most severe injury to any person involved in the crash.
Number of people with possible/non-Incapacitating/incapacitating injury in the crash.
Number of people with a fatal injury in the crash.
This is the light condition at the time of crash.
This is the roadway surface condition at the location of the first harmful event.
This is the prevailing atmospheric conditions that existed at the time of the crash.
This indicates the location of first harmful event, eg. on roadway or roadside;
This is the manner in which two motor vehicles in transport initially came together without regard to the direction of force.
This is the vehicle type indicating the general configuration or shape of the power unit involved in the motor vehicle crash.
This is the total number of occupants in, or on this vehicle involved in the crash.
This is the estimated total damage to vehicle, as result of crash.
This is the 4 digits model year of vehicle.
The make given by the manufacturer to a line of vehicles.
This is the model name or number given by the manufacturer to a given model of vehicle.
This is what the motorist/non-motorist was doing immediately prior to the crash.
This is the first event in sequence for this vehicle in crash.
This is the second event in sequence for this vehicle in crash.
This is the motorist/non-motorist?s action that may have contributed to the crash.
The posted/statutory speed limit for the motor vehicle at the time of the crash.
The speed of the motor vehicle at the time of the crash.
This is the driver injury level evaluated by law enforcement officers at the scene.
This is based on the officer?s assessment of the motorist/non-motorist?s physical or emotional condition at the time of the crash.
This is any driver distraction at the time of the crash.
This is the mode of transportation to a medical facility.
This is the airbag deployment status relative to this motorist/ occupant?s seating position
This is the record whether this motorist was completely, or partially, thrown from the passenger compartment of the motor vehicle, as a result of this crash.
